The Lagos State Traffic Management Authority (LASTMA) has warned motorists and pedestrians to exercise caution around the bridge in Ijesha area of the state. A truck is currently stuck under the bridge, with part of the pedestrian bridge which is located along the Oshodi-Apapa expressway now broken. According to a video shared by LASTMA on Wednesday, a blue truck appears to have flipped, with its dump box trapped under the bridge. Speaking on the incident on its official Twitter handle, LASTMA said the “structural integrity” of the bridge has been compromised “greatly”, and warned pedestrians to avoid using it. The agency also advised motorists plying the route to drive with utmost care. “Be advised, this truck was reported to have been stuck at Ijesha bridge inward Oshodi. Drive with care on this route,” the tweet reads. “Be advised, the structural integrity of the pedestrian bridge at Ijesha inward Oshodi has been compromised greatly, therefore it is in the interest of pedestrians to avoid it as much as possible. “Motorists plying this route, or with the intention of plying this route, need to do so with maximum caution.” #ApapaOshodi #AccidentReport Be advised, the Structural Integrity of the pedestrian bridge at Ijesha inw Oshodi has been compromised greatly, therefore it is in the interest of pedestrians to avoid it as much as possible.@LASGWorks@Gidi_Traffic @trafficbutter @TrafficChiefNG https://t.co/cYt9JzlMn9 — LASTMA (@followlastma) March 16, 2022  